/www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":54,"dimensions":55},"Crude and irregularly carved large letters. Phi has a small eye, seemingly formed of two small loops; omega is small, mid-line, open, with outward/downward sloping tails; nu is large and uneven; alpha is broad, but the form of the bar is illegible; kappa has short equal arms joined to the vertical; omicron appears small and midline.",[56,62],{"type":57,"l":58,"from":59,"to":59,"h":60,"unit":61,"atLeast":60,"atMost":60},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","59","mm",{"type":63,"l":64,"from":59,"to":65,"h":66,"unit":61},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2","NA",{"_":68,"notBefore":69,"notAfter":70,"evidence":71},"The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE or early 2nd century, offering a terminus ante quem",-350,-201,"archaeological-context",[73,79],{"_":74,"type":75,"ref":76,"corresp":77,"region":78},"Abacaenum","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462062","#findspot","Sicilia",{"_":80,"type":81,"ref":82,"offset":83,"region":78},"Tripi","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2522853","near",[85],[86,87],38.05191,15.10158,{"_":89,"type":90,"subtype":91,"xml:id":92,"geo":93},"Tomb 69/70 of the necropolis in contrada Cardusa, where it remains in situ","found","discovered","findspot",[94,95],38.06519,15.11438,[94,95],{"_":98,"type":99,"subtype":100,"geo":17},"Metcalfe 2016 visited site","observed","autopsied",[102],{"n":103,"url":104,"height":105,"width":106,"desc":107,"surfaceType":108},"screen","ISic004416_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana","front","Sicily",{"_":111,"role":112,"ref":113,"museum":114},"Necropoli di Abakainon","site","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/186",{"slug":115,"type":112,"name":111,"uri":113,"description":116,"location":117,"idno"