,{"n":103,"url":104,"height":105,"width":106,"desc":107,"surfaceType":108},[177],{"atLeast":178,"atMost":178},59,[180,181],"Bacci, Coppolino, 2009, La Necropoli di Abakainon: primi dati","Sofia, 2018, Nuove iscrizioni funerarie dalla necropoli di Abakainon",[183,184],"DX8AWC9Q","JQQKI6JP",[186,187,188,19,24,28,189,190,191,192,190,193,194,128],"isic004416","epitaph for philon, son aunakos",{"_":5},"abacaenum","tripi","sicilia","sicily","necropoli di abakainon","ancient greek",[],{"title":197,"body":198,"divs":199,"editions":224,"images":234,"handnote":240},"ISic004416. Epitaph for Philon, son Aunakos","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ฮฆฮฏฮปฯฮฝ ฮฯฬฃฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ฮฆฮฮฮฉฮฮ.ฮฮฮฮฮฅ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004416_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004416_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic004416.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana\" src=\"ISic004416-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text based upon photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Sofia 2018: ฮฆฮนฮปฮฟฬฃฮฝฮฑฬฃ[.]ฮนฬฃฮฑฬฃฮบฬฃฮฟฬฃฯฬฃ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Philon son of Aunakos\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The name ฮฆฮฏฮปฯฮฝ is extremely common; ฮฯฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ on the other hand is only attested on the other plinth of this tomb, \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004415\u003C/a>. This plinth is one of a pair on a single base - a type attested several times in this necropolis - and the second plinth (\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004415\u003C/a>) is also inscribed and the presence of the name ฮฯฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ in the genitive as its second element there suggests that the tomb is a double one for siblings. The same situation seems to be attested in the case of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004417\u003C/a> / \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004418\u003C/a>. The first name here appears to be in the nominative (which has a parallel in \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001208\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001208\u003C/a>), rather than the more commonly found genitive in this necropolis. The lettering of this text is both larger and cruder than on the companion text, and less carefully set out, suggesting a different hand.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Bacci and Coppolino 2009 28 fig.15 (and ref on p.113) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 107 no.6 and fig.7 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Crude and irregularly carved large letters. Phi has a small eye, seemingly formed of two small loops; omega is small, mid-line, open, with outward/downward sloping tails; nu is large and uneven; alpha is broad, but the form of the bar is illegible; kappa has short equal arms joined to the vertical; omicron appears small and midline.\u003C/p> Line 1  59  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[200,203,206,209,212,215,218,221],{"id":201,"html":202},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ฮฆฮฏฮปฯฮฝ ฮฯฬฃฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ฮฆฮฮฮฉฮฮ.ฮฮฮฮฮฅ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":204,"html":205},