k\">ISic004417\u003C/a> / \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004418\u003C/a>. The first name here appears to be in the nominative (which has a parallel in \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001208\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001208\u003C/a>), rather than the more commonly found genitive in this necropolis. The lettering of this text is both larger and cruder than on the companion text, and less carefully set out, suggesting a different hand.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":216,"html":217},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Bacci and Coppolino 2009 28 fig.15 (and ref on p.113) \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2018 107 no.6 and fig.7 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":219,"html":220},"handnote","\u003Cp>Crude and irregularly carved large letters. Phi has a small eye, seemingly formed of two small loops; omega is small, mid-line, open, with outward/downward sloping tails; nu is large and uneven; alpha is broad, but the form of the bar is illegible; kappa has short equal arms joined to the vertical; omicron appears small and midline.\u003C/p> Line 1  59  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  ",{"id":222,"html":223},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[225,227,230,231],{"html":226},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":228,"lang":128,"html":229},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>ฮฆฮฏฮปฯฮฝ ฮฯฬฃฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"h