                \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>Plinth (support for a stele) with mouldings top and bottom, of the local sandstone; the upper moulding is damaged, principally at the corners. The plinth is the right one of a pair mounted on a single base, classified as an epitymbion of type C.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.inorganic.stone\" type=\"stone.unspecified\" subtype=\"unverified\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/75.html\">sandstone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.arch_element.plinth\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/1910.html\">plinth\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">33\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">60\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">71\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Single line of greek letters approximately centred on the face of the plinth, descending to right\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Crude and irregularly carved large letters. Phi has a small eye, seemingly formed of two small loops; omega is small, mid-line, open, with outward/downward sloping tails; nu is large and uneven; alpha is broad, but the form of the bar is illegible; kappa has short equal arms joined to the vertical; omicron appears small and midline.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"59\" atMost=\"59\">59\u003C/height>\u003C!--from Sofia 2018-->\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\">NA\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462062\" corresp=\"#findspot\">Abacaenum\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003Coffset>near\n                                    \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2522853\">Tripi\u003C/placeName>\n                                \u003C/offset>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>38.05191, 15.10158\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0350\" notAfter-custom=\"-0201\" evidence=\"archaeological-context\">The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE or early 2nd century, offering a terminus ante quem\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" xml:id=\"findspot\">Tomb 69/70 of the necropolis in contrada Cardusa\u003Cgeo>38.065190, 15.114380\u003C/geo>, where it remains in situ\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Metcalfe 2016 visited site\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                 \u003Cchange when=\"2020-05-27\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created the file from template, publications, and photographs\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2020-09-10\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-21\" who=\"#JP\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic004416_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic004416.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dellโIdentitร  Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>ฮฆฮฏฮปฯฮฝ ฮ\u003Cunclear>ฯ\u003C/unclear>ฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n               \u003ClistApp>\n                   \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text based upon photographs\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                   \u003Capp loc=\"line 1\">\u003Cnote>Sofia 2018: ฮฆฮนฮป\u003Cunclear>ฮฟ\u003C/unclear>ฮฝ\u003Cunclear>ฮฑ\u003C/unclear>[.]\u003Cunclear>ฮนฮฑฮบฮฟฯ\u003C/unclear>\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n               \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>Philon son of Aunakos\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>The name ฮฆฮฏฮปฯฮฝ is extremely common; ฮฯฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ on the other hand is only attested on the other plinth of this tomb, \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\">ISic004415\u003C/ref>. This plinth is one of a pair on a single base - a type attested several times in this necropolis - and the second plinth (\u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004415\">ISic004415\u003C/ref>) is also inscribed and the presence of the name ฮฯฮฝฮฑฮบฮฟฯ in the genitive as its second element there suggests that the tomb is a double one for siblings.  The same situation seems to be attested in the case of \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004417\">ISic004417\u003C/ref> / \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004418\">ISic004418\u003C/ref>. The first name here appears to be in the nominative (which has a parallel in \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001208\">ISic001208\u003C/ref>), rather than the more commonly found genitive in this necropolis. The lettering of this text is both larger and cruder than on the companion text, and less carefully set out, suggesting a different hand.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Bacci and Coppolino\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2009\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>28 fig.15 (and ref on p.113)\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/DX8AWC9Q\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002171\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Sofia\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>2018\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>107 no.6 and fig.7\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JQQKI6JP\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001574\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
